Introduction In this paper we present OACIS (Organizing Assistant for Comprehensive and Interactive Simulations) [1], an open-source job management software for large-scale simulations (http://github.com/crest-cassia/oacis ).
The web server is developed based on the Ruby on Rails framework ( http://rubyonrails.org/ ), which provides an interactive user-interface.
MongoDB ( http://www.mongodb.org/ ), a document-based database, is used as data storage.
In order to absorb the dierence of the schedulers, we introduced a small script called \XSUB" ( https://github.com/crest-cassia/xsub ).
The rst one is running a virtual machine image in which OACIS is already set up using Docker ( https://www.docker.com/ ).
The image is built on \docker hub" (https://hub.docker.com/ ), a public site hosting docker images, which lets you start OACIS with a few commands.
For the full instruction on the installation, please refer to the documentation of OACIS (http://crest-cassia.github.io/oacis/en/install.html).

Dataset Stack Exchange (https://StackExchange.com/) is a network of questions and answer websites that contain subwebsites forspeciÔ¨Åc topics, such as computer science, German language, or workplace, to name just a few.

For instance, usernumber 5001 (https://tex.stackexchange.com/users/5001/mico) was active in all of the networks used overtime forthe Latex subwebsite, and he/she is in the top 0 09% among the whole users of Stack Exchange and have reputation score236thousands.

The same behavior was found on the Statis- tics subwebsite for user 805 (https://stats.stackexchange.com/users/805/glen-b) who is in the top 0 02% among the Stack Exchange users and have reputation score 191thou- sands.

Moreover, those two users were mainly active onother subwebsites; for example, user 932 (https://music.stackexchange.com/users/932/leftaroundabout) was foundin all of the networks of the Music dataset, but his main activ-ity was on the Stack Over Ô¨Çow subwebsites.

We investigated this behaviorand found that the Statistics subwebsite is the least activesubwebsite among all Stack Exchange subwebsites withthe fewest answered questions; that is, only 61% of thequestions were answered (https://stackexchange.com/sites),whereas on other subwebsites, the answer rate is muchhigher, for example, reaching 93% and 97% on the Latexand Music subwebsites, respectively.
